  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "carson-gross",
    "senderColor": "red",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Re-confirming consent, toHaveClass is the right call",
    "content": "I already reviewed the actual code changes and sent my consent earlier. To confirm clearly: I approve all three changes.\n\nOn the `toHaveClass(/visually-hidden/)` tradeoff -- yes, it is more implementation-specific than `not.toBeVisible()`, but it is the right call. The `.visually-hidden` class is part of our design system's accessibility contract, not an incidental implementation detail. Asserting its presence directly is more honest than asserting a visual side-effect (bounding box size) that Playwright doesn't even interpret correctly for `clip-path` elements. If someone removes that class, the test should fail -- that's exactly the behavior we want.\n\nConsensus confirmed from the HTMX perspective."
  }
}
